dataset.title: Data Download: TopoPlanimetric and Cadastral
dataset.description:
Updated Jan 2021 to include option to preview the Topoplanimetric and Cadastral data

Downloading Data:
  1. Locate your area of interest by panning and zooming the map, or using the search function in the upper-right corner of the window.
  2. Click on the map within your area of interest. A pop-up should appear for that square mile section.
  3. Click on some or all of the links to download data in ESRI Geodatabase (.gdb) or CAD Drawing (.dwg) format
  4. Once the files are downloaded, unzip them. Within the output folders will be the original source data.

Data Included (Variable Geometries; Point, Line, Polygon and Annotation):

Topographic/Planimetric Data Types:
Environmental
Structures and Bridges
Hydrology
Park
Survey Control
Elevation Contours
Transportation Features
Utility Features

Cadastral Data Types:
Hydrologic Tax Parcels
Condominium
Certified Survey Map (CSM)
Subdivisions
Tax Parcels
Rights-of-Way

Still Looking for More Data? Check out https://gis-mclio.opendata.arcgis.com/

dataset.title: 2020 Aerial Imagery
dataset.description:
3-inch ortho-rectified vertical aerial photography covering Milwaukee County Wisconsin - captured April 2020.

The dataset consists of tiled orthogonal imagery produced from nadir images captured by Pictometry International. Automatic aerial triangulation (AAT) was performed. The triangulated frames were rectified to a LiDAR derived DEM. Mosaicking was performed using an automatic seaming algorithm and manually edited to eliminate seams through elevated features where possible.
dataset.license: Use of this data is constrained by the license agreements between Pictometry International and Milwaukee County.

dataset.title: Coastal County Data for Download
dataset.description:
Download a file geodatabase of coastal, bluff, and asset data created for Wisconsin Coastal Resiliency Grant report.

To view and interact with the data without downloading, use our interactive web map: http://mclio.maps.arcgis.com/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=370390c8ee524135b51c5f849865901d

The database includes all the mapped county owned assets located within the defined coastal zone. The assets list the assessed condition, vulnerability, and resiliency ratings in the featureâ€™s attribute data. It also includes the supporting GIS data used to complete the analysis, for example, shoreline protection polygons and their ratings from GZA, coastal bluff crest and toe lines, bluff recession data, and shoreline lines. The county site bluff data is also provided.

dataset.title: 2013 Aerial Photo
dataset.description: The dataset consists of tiled orthogonal imagery produced from nadir images captured by Pictometry International during the period of April 16th, 2013 to May 4th, 2013. Automatic aerial triangulation (AAT) was performed. The triangulated frames were rectified to a Pictometry Produced LiDAR derived DEM. Mosaicing was performed using an automatic seaming algorithm and manually edited to eliminate seams through elevated features where possible.

dataset.title: 2010 Aerial Photo
dataset.description: The dataset consists of tiled orthogonal imagery produced from nadir images captured by Pictometry International during the period of April 10th, 2010 to April 23rd, 2010. Automatic aerial triangulation (AAT) was performed. The triangulated frames were rectified to a Pictometry Produced LiDAR derived DEM. Mosaicing was performed using an automatic seaming algorithm and manually edited to eliminate seams through elevated features where possible.

dataset.title: 2015 Aerial Photo
dataset.description: Pictometry flew the countywide area from March 16 - March 30, 2015, and recaptured small areas in which ice or snow obscured the imagery the following spring. This image is representative of the two sets of data, blended together by Pictometry after collection.

dataset.title: LiDAR Data Downloads and Derived Datasets
dataset.description: A website that highlights different types of LIDAR-derived datasets and includes LiDAR data downloads for 2020, 2015, and 2010. Each dataset has its own page that features a web map with the data in it, and links to where the data is available.
